<inglise> 92/562/EEC: Commission Decision of 17 November 1992 on the approval of alternative heat treatment systems for processing high-risk material </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS 92/562/EM&Uuml; alternatiivsete kuumt&ouml;&ouml;tlemiss&uuml;steemide tunnustamise kohta k&otilde;rge riskiteguriga materjali t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel 17. november 1992 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 90/667/EEC of 27 November 1990 laying down the veterinary rules for the disposal and processing of animal waste, for its placing on the market and for the prevention of pathogens in feedstuffs of animal or fish origin and amending Directive 90/425/EEC (1), and in particular Annex II, Chapter II, paragraph 6 (c) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 27. novembri 1990. aasta direktiivi 90/667/EM&Uuml;, millega n&auml;hakse ette veterinaareeskirjad loomsete j&auml;&auml;tmete k&otilde;rvaldamise, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise ja turuleviimise kohta ning haigustekitajate v&auml;ltimise kohta loomset p&auml;ritolu v&otilde;i kalast valmistatud s&ouml;&ouml;tades ning muudetakse direktiivi 90/425/EM&Uuml;, (1) eriti selle II lisa II peat&uuml;ki l&otilde;ike 6 punkti c, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas paragraph 6 (a) of Annex II, Chapter II of Directive 90/667/EEC requires that high-risk material must be heated to a core temperature of at least 133 &deg;C for 20 minutes at a pressure of 3 bar after the particle size of the raw material has been reduced to at least 50 mm; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: direktiivi 90/667/EM&Uuml; II lisa II peat&uuml;ki l&otilde;ike 6 punktis a n&otilde;utakse, et k&otilde;rge riskiteguriga materjali tuleb p&auml;rast tooraine peenestamist v&auml;hemalt 50 mm osakesteks kuumutada sisetemperatuurini v&auml;hemalt 133 &deg;C ning hoida nimetatud temperatuuril ja 3baarise r&otilde;hu juures 20 minutit; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to define with precision the alternative systems of heat treatment offering guarantees in conformity with the requirements under Directive 90/667/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja t&auml;pselt m&auml;&auml;ratleda alternatiivsed kuumt&ouml;&ouml;tlemiss&uuml;steemid, millega tagatakse vastavus direktiivi 90/667/EM&Uuml; n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Decision are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Veterinary Committee, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva otsusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las alalise veterinaarkomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Plants processing high-risk material using a system, or a combination of systems, described in the Annex may be approved by the competent authority provided that they can meet the terms and conditions of Directive 90/667/EEG and where it has been demonstrated to the competent authority that the final product has been sampled on a daily basis over a period of one month in compliance with the microbiological standards laid down in Annex II, Chapter III (1) and (2) of the aforementioned Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;devad asutused v&otilde;ivad tunnustada k&otilde;rge riskiteguriga materjali t&ouml;&ouml;tlevaid tehaseid, mis kasutavad lisas kirjeldatud s&uuml;steemi v&otilde;i s&uuml;steemide kombinatsiooni, tingimusel et need tehased vastavad direktiivi 90/667/EM&Uuml; tingimustele ning p&auml;devale asutusele on t&otilde;endatud, et l&otilde;pptootest &uuml;he kuu jooksul iga p&auml;ev v&otilde;etud proovid vastavad eespool nimetatud direktiivi II lisa III peat&uuml;ki l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud mikrobioloogilistele standarditele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Details of the critical control points under which each plant satisfactorily complies with the microbiological standards shall be recorded and maintained so that the owner, operator or his representative and, as necessary, the competent authority can monitor the operation of the plant. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;ksikasjad kriitiliste kontrollpunktide kohta, mille alusel tehased rahuldavalt vastavad mikrobioloogilistele standarditele, registreeritakse ja s&auml;ilitatakse, et omanik, ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema esindaja ning vajaduse korral p&auml;dev asutus saaks j&auml;lgida ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> The information to be recorded and monitored shall include the particle size, critical temperature and, as appropriate, the absolute time, pressure profile, raw material feed-rate and fat recycling rate. </inglise>
<eesti> Registreeritav ja j&auml;lgitav teave h&otilde;lmab osakese suurust, kriitilist temperatuuri ning vastavalt vajadusele absoluutset aega, r&otilde;hku, tooraine etteandmise kiirust ja rasva ringlemiskiirust. </eesti>
<inglise> This information shall be made available to the Commission on request. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealune teave tuleb teha komisjoni n&otilde;udmisel talle k&auml;ttesaadavaks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 17 November 1992. For the Commission </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 17. november 1992 </eesti>
